Needs a live Kubernetes cluster: the `cluster` datasource auto-connects on
startup, so without one the app logs a connect ERROR and the shared "clean
startup" check fails. The published-binary BDD runner (macOS, no cluster) can't
provide one. Run it explicitly with a cluster up (see cluster/):
  ./apps/periscope/cluster/start.sh && ./apps/periscope/cluster/ingress.sh
  cargo run -p test-framework -- apps/periscope
